The ODM National Election Board has been urged to learn from the mistakes of nominations in other counties and conduct a credible exercise in Kisumu.The Kisumu nominations will be on Monday.Nominations in parts of Nyanza and Western have been marred by confusion, delays, missing names &ndash; of aspirants and party members &ndash; and claims of rigging.&ldquo;We have seen what has happened in Nyamira and Busia but hope that with each nomination day the party continues to learn something new,&rdquo; governor aspirant Hezron Mc&rsquo;Obewa said. &ldquo;Kisumu is hotly contested and it is ODM&rsquo;s headquarters in Western Kenya [so] we hope to have a credible nomination.&rdquo;He spoke on the campaign trail in Kisumu on Wednesday.